alerts.title: Beach Hazards Statement for San Francisco, CA
alerts.description:
...LONG PERIOD SWELL ARRIVING AT THE COAST...
AN ACTIVE NORTH PACIFIC HAS GENERATED SIGNIFICANT WAVE ACTION THAT
IS ARRIVING ALONG THE CENTRAL CALIFORNIA COAST THIS MORNING AS
LONG PERIOD NORTHWEST SWELL.
...BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM PST THIS
EVENING...
THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE IN SAN FRANCISCO HAS ISSUED A BEACH
HAZARDS STATEMENT FOR SNEAKER WAVES AND INCREASED RIP
CURRENTS...WHICH IS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM PST THIS EVENING.
* HAZARDS...LONG PERIOD ENERGETIC SWELL.
* TIMING...THROUGH TODAY.
* LOCATION...ALL WEST AND NORTHWEST FACING BEACHES.
* POTENTIAL IMPACTS...MODERATE RISK OF SNEAKER WAVES AND AN
INCREASED THREAT OF RIP CURRENTS.
